 237:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****  * is important its value is not updated due to a task priority change while it is
 238:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****  * being used for another purpose.  The following bit definition is used to inform
 239:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****  * the scheduler that the value should not be changed - in which case it is the
 240:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****  * responsibility of whichever module is using the value to ensure it gets set back
 241:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****  * to its original value when it is released. */
 242:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c **** #if ( configUSE_16_BIT_TICKS == 1 )
 243:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****     #define taskEVENT_LIST_ITEM_VALUE_IN_USE    0x8000U
 244:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c **** #else
 245:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c ****     #define taskEVENT_LIST_ITEM_VALUE_IN_USE    0x80000000UL
 246:middlewares/freertos/source/tasks.c **** #endif
